Process for Measuring Adherence to Your Specific WebSocket Controls

Based on your defined controls, here's a tailored measurement process:

Control Adherence Measurement Matrix

Control 1: WSS Only Enforcement

Measurement Process:

```
Frequency: Continuous monitoring + Quarterly audit
```

· Technical Validation:
  · Configure load balancer/WAF to reject WS (non-TLS) connections
  · Implement server-side check during WebSocket handshake:
    ```javascript
    // Server-side validation
    if (request.headers['x-forwarded-proto'] !== 'https') {
      rejectConnection('WSS required');
    }
    ```
· Monitoring Metrics:
  · WSS_Compliance_Rate = (WSS_connections / Total_WebSocket_attempts) × 100
  · Target: 100%
· Alerting:
  · Immediate alert for any successful WS (non-TLS) connection
  · Daily report of attempted WS connections

Control 2: Unique Token Per Request with Server-Side Validation

Measurement Process:

```
Frequency: Real-time validation + Weekly audit
```

· Validation Checks:
  · Implement token generation/validation middleware
  · Log all token validation attempts (success/failure)
  · Monitor token reuse attempts
· Testing Procedures:
  · Automated tests that attempt:
    · Reusing tokens
    · Using expired tokens
    · Using invalid tokens
    · Missing tokens
· Metrics to Track:
  · Token validation failure rate
  · Average token lifetime
  · Token reuse attempts count
· Sample Implementation:
  ```javascript
  // Measurement endpoint
  app.get('/metrics/token-validation', (req, res) => {
    res.json({
      total_requests: tokenMetrics.total,
      valid_tokens: tokenMetrics.valid,
      invalid_tokens: tokenMetrics.invalid,
      reused_tokens: tokenMetrics.reused,
      compliance_rate: (tokenMetrics.valid / tokenMetrics.total) * 100
    });
  });
  ```

Control 3: Session Management/Timeout

Measurement Process:

```
Frequency: Daily monitoring + Monthly review
```

· Configuration Verification:
  · Document and validate session timeout settings
  · Ensure idle and absolute timeout configurations
· Monitoring Setup:
  · Track connection duration statistics
  · Alert on sessions exceeding max duration
  · Monitor reconnection patterns
· Metrics Dashboard:
  ```
  Average session duration: [actual] vs [expected]
  Sessions terminated by timeout: [count]
  Max concurrent sessions per user: [number]
  Session renewal rate: [percentage]
  ```
· Testing Protocol:
  · Simulate idle connections beyond timeout
  · Test session cleanup procedures
  · Verify session data isolation

Control 4: WAF Traffic Inspection

Measurement Process:

```
Frequency: Real-time + Weekly audit
```

· Verification Steps:
  1. Configuration Audit:
     · Verify WAF rules enable WebSocket inspection
     · Check WAF is positioned in traffic path
     · Validate WebSocket-specific rules
  2. Traffic Flow Validation:
     · Use traceroute/tcpdump to confirm routing
     · Deploy canary connections with known malicious payloads
  3. Effectiveness Testing:
     · Send test malicious WebSocket frames
     · Verify WAF blocks/rejects them
· Key Metrics:
  · WAF_WebSocket_Block_Rate = (Blocked_WS_requests / Total_malicious_attempts) × 100
  · WAF latency impact on WebSocket connections
  · False positive rate for legitimate traffic
· Reporting:
  · Weekly WAF effectiveness report
  · Monthly blocked attack patterns analysis

Control 5: Destination Allow-Listing/Hardcoding

Measurement Process:

```
Frequency: Pre-deployment + Monthly audit
```

· Client-Side Verification:
  · Static Analysis: Scan client code for dynamic WebSocket URL construction
  · Build Process: Implement checks for hardcoded URLs
  · Deployment Validation: Verify production URLs match allow-list
· Server-Side Enforcement:
  · Log all connection origins
  · Reject connections to non-allow-listed destinations
· Testing Approach:
  ```javascript
  // Test cases to run
  const testCases = [
    { url: 'wss://approved-domain.com', expected: 'allowed' },
    { url: 'wss://malicious-domain.com', expected: 'blocked' },
    { url: 'wss://' + userInput + '.com', expected: 'blocked' }
  ];
  ```
· Compliance Metrics:
  · Percentage of clients using approved endpoints
  · Attempts to connect to non-approved destinations
  · Dynamic URL construction detection rate

Control 6: Origin Header Validation

Measurement Process:

```
Frequency: Real-time + Daily monitoring
```

· Implementation Verification:
  · Ensure Origin header validation occurs during handshake
  · Maintain allow-list of valid origins
  · Implement strict validation (not just prefix matching)
· Monitoring Configuration:
  · Log all Origin headers received
  · Alert on validation failures
  · Track patterns of malicious origin attempts
· Testing Suite:
  ```bash
  # Test script for Origin validation
  curl -i -N \
    -H "Origin: https://evil.com" \
    -H "Connection: Upgrade" \
    -H "Upgrade: websocket" \
    https://your-websocket-server.com
  # Should be rejected
  ```
· Key Metrics:
  · Origin_Validation_Success_Rate = (Valid_origins / Total_connections) × 100
  · Top rejected origins (for threat intelligence)
  · Geographic patterns of invalid origin attempts

