Audit Checklist

```
Quarterly Security Audit - WebSocket Controls

1. WSS Enforcement:
   [ ] All environments enforce WSS
   [ ] No WS endpoints exposed
   [ ] Certificate validity > 30 days

2. Token Validation:
   [ ] Token generation algorithm reviewed
   [ ] Validation logic penetration tested
   [ ] Token storage/transmission secure

3. Session Management:
   [ ] Timeout values appropriate for use case
   [ ] Session cleanup verified
   [ ] No memory leaks in session handling

4. WAF Inspection:
   [ ] WAF rules updated for WebSocket threats
   [ ] Inspection covers all WebSocket traffic
   [ ] Performance impact within SLA

5. Destination Control:
   [ ] Client code scanned for dynamic URLs
   [ ] Allow-list reviewed and updated
   [ ] No client-side URL manipulation possible

6. Origin Validation:
   [ ] Validation occurs before handshake completion
   [ ] Allow-list of origins current
   [ ] CSWSH protection effective
```

Remediation Workflow

```
When control adherence < 95%:
1. Immediate: Alert security team
2. Within 1 hour: Isolate affected component
3. Within 4 hours: Root cause analysis
4. Within 24 hours: Remediation plan
5. Within 72 hours: Control restored
6. Within 1 week: Process improvement to prevent recurrence
```

Tooling Recommendations Specific to Your Controls

1. For Token Validation:
   · Use JWT with short expiration
   · Implement Redis for token blacklisting
   · Deploy Open Policy Agent for policy enforcement
2. For WAF Inspection:
   · Configure ModSecurity with OWASP CRS
   · Implement AWS WAF or Cloudflare WebSocket rules
   · Use specialized WebSocket security tools like ThreatMapper
3. For Origin Validation:
   · Implement strict CORS policies
   · Use middleware like helmet and cors with strict settings
   · Deploy reverse proxy with origin validation

Evidence Collection for Compliance

For each control, maintain:

· Configuration snapshots
· Test execution logs
· Monitoring dashboard screenshots
· Incident response records
· Third-party penetration test reports

This process ensures you can measure, prove, and maintain adherence to your specific WebSocket security controls effectively.